 The South African National Roads Agency SOC Ltd (SANRAL) would like to notify road users that the Nico Malan pass, between Seymour and Whittlesea on the R67, in the Eastern Cape will be closed until  3pm today, 15 February 2017, due to an accident. “Motorists are asked use caution when making use of the road,” said Mbulelo Peterson, SANRAL Southern Region Manager. SANRAL apologises for any inconvenience caused.  